[Episode 11: Miss Korea]

00:01:58.430 --> 00:02:00.060
Try this.

00:02:00.060 --> 00:02:02.480
A friend gave me this pu'er tea.

00:02:02.480 --> 00:02:05.390
It's a fermented tea which is good for you.

00:02:05.390 --> 00:02:07.040
The aroma is quite nice.

00:02:07.040 --> 00:02:08.910
Thank you.

00:02:18.350 --> 00:02:20.330
"Why did you call me here?"

00:02:20.330 --> 00:02:22.620
"Don't beat around the bush and get to the point."

00:02:22.620 --> 00:02:25.160
That's how you're looking at me. Am I wrong?

00:02:25.160 --> 00:02:28.130
I have a client appointment coming up soon.

00:02:28.130 --> 00:02:30.710
Okay. I'll get to the point.

00:02:35.520 --> 00:02:37.250
Ko Yeong Rye.

00:02:37.250 --> 00:02:40.410
Let's cause a little trouble together.

00:02:40.410 --> 00:02:43.130
Trouble? What kind of trouble?

00:02:43.130 --> 00:02:45.910
How about entering Miss Korea?

00:02:45.910 --> 00:02:47.230
Sorry?

00:02:47.230 --> 00:02:50.930
There is a candidate our shop has been supporting.

00:02:50.930 --> 00:02:56.110
But after 20 years of producing Miss Koreas,

00:02:56.110 --> 00:02:58.700
I feel something is missing.

00:02:58.700 --> 00:03:02.140
You could fill that gap.

00:03:02.140 --> 00:03:03.330
What do you think?

00:03:03.330 --> 00:03:07.520
D-Director, it's something
I've never even dreamed of.

00:03:07.520 --> 00:03:09.590
Then, start thinking about it now.

00:03:09.590 --> 00:03:12.120
This weekend is the prelim application deadline.

00:03:12.120 --> 00:03:14.310
Compared to the girls
who are artificially polished,

00:03:14.310 --> 00:03:19.120
I think you're way more natural and fresh.

00:03:21.700 --> 00:03:23.180
Director, I-

00:03:23.180 --> 00:03:27.400
In your interview, you said your dream
was to go to college, right?

00:03:27.400 --> 00:03:28.960
If you win the Miss Korea crown,

00:03:28.960 --> 00:03:32.320
you get 15 million won in scholarship.

00:03:32.320 --> 00:03:34.190
I heard you've been working

00:03:34.190 --> 00:03:37.390
and squeezing in time to study for night school.

00:03:37.390 --> 00:03:39.140
But when will you get there?

00:03:40.300 --> 00:03:44.430
Isn't that motivation enough?

00:03:47.540 --> 00:03:49.490
I'm in favor.

00:03:49.490 --> 00:03:51.610
You wanted to attend college.

00:03:51.610 --> 00:03:54.370
If your financial situation is resolved,
you could focus on the exams.

00:03:54.370 --> 00:03:56.520
Even if you don't place,

00:03:56.520 --> 00:03:59.400
I think it'll be a good life experience.

00:03:59.400 --> 00:04:02.860
Taking on challenges is your specialty.

00:04:03.710 --> 00:04:07.730
Aren't you Ko Yeong Rye as in
"Go all in, no matter what"?

00:04:07.730 --> 00:04:09.590
But still.

00:04:09.590 --> 00:04:13.420
This is too big a challenge.

00:04:13.420 --> 00:04:17.070
Me, Miss Korea? Not in my wildest dreams.

00:04:17.070 --> 00:04:19.020
Not in your wildest dreams?

00:04:19.020 --> 00:04:21.390
Why not? What's the problem?

00:04:21.390 --> 00:04:23.760
You're already Jin in my eyes.

00:04:23.760 --> 00:04:27.090
Come on. I'm being serious.

00:04:27.090 --> 00:04:30.110
All right. What about your mom?

00:04:30.110 --> 00:04:32.790
Did you tell her yet?

00:04:32.790 --> 00:04:35.260
No, not yet.

00:04:35.260 --> 00:04:38.320
My mom will probably flip.

00:04:39.900 --> 00:04:44.400
But should I still discuss it with her?

00:04:45.770 --> 00:04:48.650
I should, shouldn't I?

00:04:57.960 --> 00:05:00.260
You must be tired. I told you to go up.

00:05:00.260 --> 00:05:02.830
Why the hell won't you listen?

00:05:02.830 --> 00:05:05.560
I'm better off doing it alone.

00:05:08.250 --> 00:05:11.710
What? You've got something to say to me?

00:05:12.750 --> 00:05:15.280
I'm telling you, you're psychic.

00:05:15.280 --> 00:05:16.930
If you started telling fortunes,

00:05:16.930 --> 00:05:19.820
every fortune teller in this town
would go out of business.

00:05:19.820 --> 00:05:24.700
Goodness. You're dragging this out too much.

00:05:24.700 --> 00:05:28.460
Cut the nonsense and spit it out.

00:05:28.460 --> 00:05:30.110
What is it?

00:05:35.510 --> 00:05:41.990
So that missile or Mitchell, or whatever...

00:05:41.990 --> 00:05:44.960
said you should try for Miss Korea?

00:05:44.960 --> 00:05:46.590
Yeah.

00:05:46.590 --> 00:05:51.100
If I win the crown, I could win scholarship money.

00:05:51.100 --> 00:05:53.940
- Fifteen million won.
- F-Fifteen million won?

00:05:53.940 --> 00:05:59.270
With that money, we could deal
with the increased rent

00:05:59.270 --> 00:06:01.310
and cover living costs and tuition.

00:06:01.310 --> 00:06:06.560
Then, I could go all-in on entrance prep and...

00:06:06.560 --> 00:06:10.500
And? Why are you trailing off?

00:06:10.500 --> 00:06:12.790
If I don't make it...

00:06:13.940 --> 00:06:18.590
But if I get to the main round and don't rank,

00:06:19.590 --> 00:06:22.480
I can't work during the training period,

00:06:22.480 --> 00:06:25.150
and I won't get paid.

00:06:25.150 --> 00:06:27.620
I'll have wasted time for nothing.

00:06:28.520 --> 00:06:31.150
Then, I can't help you
with living expenses, either.

00:06:31.150 --> 00:06:33.060
Don't worry about living expenses.

00:06:33.060 --> 00:06:34.350
How can I not?

00:06:34.350 --> 00:06:37.590
I know you're barely keeping up with the rent.

00:06:37.590 --> 00:06:40.150
Still, don't worry this time.

00:06:47.870 --> 00:06:50.970
Don't worry about living expenses.

00:06:50.970 --> 00:06:53.410
If you want to do it, do it.

00:06:54.420 --> 00:06:57.490
If it doesn't work out, so be it.

00:07:01.340 --> 00:07:07.510
Do you know what I said to you
the most while raising you?

00:07:08.510 --> 00:07:10.800
"Don't."

00:07:10.800 --> 00:07:12.660
"Do it later."

00:07:14.660 --> 00:07:19.470
Back then, I was killing myself
feeding five mouths.

00:07:20.680 --> 00:07:22.580
I needed you to chip in.

00:07:22.580 --> 00:07:26.030
Gosh, what can you do...

00:07:27.340 --> 00:07:29.650
If you had studied with your brain,

00:07:29.650 --> 00:07:32.940
you'd already have made it big by now.

00:07:34.010 --> 00:07:38.200
When you were young, you were
busy yelling, "All right!"

00:07:39.020 --> 00:07:42.290
And now, you're busy cutting other people's hair.

00:07:50.570 --> 00:07:54.750
For once, I wanted to tell you to go for it.

00:07:56.630 --> 00:08:00.480
You're at an age when you'd want
to do so many things.

00:08:01.465 --> 00:08:04.300
Why are you getting all sentimental
all of a sudden, Mom?

00:08:04.300 --> 00:08:07.650
Because that's how I feel, you brat.

00:08:08.880 --> 00:08:10.630
So go for it.

00:08:10.630 --> 00:08:12.530
Miss Korea or whatever.

00:08:12.530 --> 00:08:15.910
I'm going to back you properly this time.

00:08:15.910 --> 00:08:19.880
As for living expenses, let the
damn dogs worry about that.

00:08:20.750 --> 00:08:22.460
Really?

00:08:24.710 --> 00:08:27.290
I can really try?

00:08:28.658 --> 00:08:30.340
Even if I might not make it?

00:08:30.340 --> 00:08:33.430
Why start by thinking you won't?

00:08:33.430 --> 00:08:36.670
If you're going for it,
believe you'll win the damn thing.

00:08:37.518 --> 00:08:41.340
Then, I'm really going for it, Mom.

00:08:45.460 --> 00:08:47.640
I'll do my best.

00:08:47.640 --> 00:08:50.360
I'll give it everything I've got.

00:08:52.770 --> 00:08:55.450
Thank you, Mom.

00:08:56.920 --> 00:08:59.340
Yeah, you'd better thank me.

00:08:59.340 --> 00:09:03.790
You got that offer because you resemble me.

00:09:03.790 --> 00:09:08.360
Your figure, your face. You've got it all.

00:09:08.360 --> 00:09:12.930
And back in my day, my height was
considered tall. You know?

00:09:15.600 --> 00:09:19.330
Gosh, my daughter is competing for Miss Korea.

00:09:19.330 --> 00:09:21.270
[Michelle Beauty Salon]

00:09:21.270 --> 00:09:25.120
I'll give it a shot, Director.

00:09:25.120 --> 00:09:30.060
I'll give Miss Korea a shot.

00:09:30.060 --> 00:09:33.000
Good. You made the right choice.

00:09:36.440 --> 00:09:39.830
Let me create a masterpiece.

00:10:27.120 --> 00:10:28.730
Oppa!

00:10:30.430 --> 00:10:32.220
You must find this fun.

00:10:32.220 --> 00:10:34.430
Showing up out of the blue.

00:10:34.430 --> 00:10:35.820
Yes, it's fun.

00:10:35.820 --> 00:10:38.740
Watching you tearing out in a rush.

00:10:40.180 --> 00:10:43.500
Doesn't your brain feel fried
after studying all day?

00:10:43.500 --> 00:10:46.530
Do you want to unwind with me again?

00:10:59.120 --> 00:11:01.150
Keep your eye on the ball.

00:11:04.370 --> 00:11:06.830
It's all about timing.

00:11:06.830 --> 00:11:09.890
Focus. Timing!

00:11:11.930 --> 00:11:14.300
Your batting average is way down today.

00:11:14.300 --> 00:11:15.910
Tell me about it.

00:11:15.910 --> 00:11:18.730
It's not going my way.

00:11:18.730 --> 00:11:20.790
Can you try it?

00:11:20.790 --> 00:11:23.230
I've got no energy left.

00:11:27.650 --> 00:11:30.570
Wow! You're so good! So good!

00:11:31.660 --> 00:11:34.040
Whoa!

00:11:41.830 --> 00:11:43.590
This is good.

00:11:43.590 --> 00:11:45.800
Are you sure?

00:11:45.800 --> 00:11:49.990
Half of it is melted. I shouldn't
have bought you ice cream.

00:11:49.990 --> 00:11:53.160
Why? I'm trying my best here.

00:11:55.720 --> 00:11:58.110
Don't force it.

00:11:58.110 --> 00:12:00.310
You're having a hard time right now.

00:12:19.790 --> 00:12:21.880
Want to sit for a minute?

00:12:30.230 --> 00:12:34.910
You really are a Seo Jong Hui specialist.

00:12:37.380 --> 00:12:39.390
To be honest,

00:12:39.390 --> 00:12:43.730
I came today, so you'd notice
what a rough time I'm having.

00:12:43.730 --> 00:12:45.230
Why?

00:12:45.230 --> 00:12:48.450
What's troubling you this time?

00:12:48.450 --> 00:12:50.870
Too many things.

00:12:51.870 --> 00:12:55.950
Hope, disappointment, greed,

00:12:55.950 --> 00:12:59.060
jealousy, love.

00:13:01.040 --> 00:13:05.430
And that blurry feeling where you love
someone but also resent them.

00:13:07.520 --> 00:13:11.960
I think people struggle because
we're creatures of emotion.

00:13:11.960 --> 00:13:16.210
You can push through other hardships,
but when it comes to emotions...

00:13:17.650 --> 00:13:20.880
They're hard to control.

00:13:20.880 --> 00:13:23.190
That's right.

00:13:24.240 --> 00:13:28.180
The heart is hard to control. Even if it's my own.

00:13:29.750 --> 00:13:31.890
Looking back,

00:13:33.270 --> 00:13:37.550
I think timing is the most important.

00:13:37.550 --> 00:13:40.690
Even in baseball, you have to swing in time,

00:13:40.690 --> 00:13:43.680
or your average tanks. Like today.

00:13:43.680 --> 00:13:48.260
But you had a great pinch-hitter
with perfect timing today.

00:13:49.880 --> 00:13:53.320
You're right. You were there for me.

00:13:55.920 --> 00:13:58.870
I've come to realize something in my life.

00:13:58.870 --> 00:14:02.900
Now is just as important as timing.

00:14:02.900 --> 00:14:08.600
What I'm doing now ultimately
creates my next chance.

00:14:09.660 --> 00:14:14.120
So, there's still a chance.

00:14:16.330 --> 00:14:18.240
You think so?

00:14:22.380 --> 00:14:25.390
I'm glad I came to you.

00:14:26.850 --> 00:14:33.490
I think my heart feels so much relief
after talking to you.

00:14:33.490 --> 00:14:35.210
You need to get back, right?

00:14:35.210 --> 00:14:37.600
No, I'm going straight home today.

00:14:37.600 --> 00:14:41.500
Want to come eat at my mom's?
You can see Yeong Rye, too.

00:14:42.900 --> 00:14:44.720
No.

00:14:44.720 --> 00:14:46.690
Not today.

00:14:46.690 --> 00:14:48.070
All right.

00:14:48.970 --> 00:14:51.010
Did you hear?

00:14:51.010 --> 00:14:53.280
Yeong Rye is entering Miss Korea.

00:14:53.280 --> 00:14:54.960
Miss Korea?

00:14:54.960 --> 00:14:57.960
Yeah. Her salon director suggested it.

00:14:57.960 --> 00:15:00.820
Sounds like she's going for it.

00:15:00.820 --> 00:15:04.140
Always so left-field, that Ko Yeong Rye.

00:15:04.140 --> 00:15:07.470
She bolts somewhere I never see coming.

00:15:21.080 --> 00:15:23.340
[Daeyang Group]

00:15:26.920 --> 00:15:30.050
What brings you here without notice?

00:15:31.080 --> 00:15:34.890
Did you come because you feel bad
about making me worry for days?

00:15:38.190 --> 00:15:40.180
Do you want to eat before going home?

00:15:40.180 --> 00:15:42.630
No, it's not that.

00:15:48.600 --> 00:15:51.690
- Mom.
- Yeah?

00:15:51.690 --> 00:15:53.760
I want to enter Miss Korea.

00:15:53.760 --> 00:15:54.910
What?

00:15:54.910 --> 00:15:57.530
I'm going to enter the Miss Korea pageant.

00:15:57.530 --> 00:16:00.760
What Jullee Salon's owner proposed last time.

00:16:06.500 --> 00:16:09.980
It's been a dream I've had since I was little.

00:16:10.890 --> 00:16:15.540
When I got the offer,
my heart raced with anticipation,

00:16:15.540 --> 00:16:18.540
but I dropped it because you were against it.

00:16:21.200 --> 00:16:24.210
But I want to try.

00:16:24.210 --> 00:16:26.000
I'll enter.

00:16:27.290 --> 00:16:29.660
Please let me enter the pageant.

00:16:31.590 --> 00:16:34.690
Are you confident you can win the crown?

00:16:38.430 --> 00:16:40.630
As Yang Mi Sook's daughter,

00:16:42.130 --> 00:16:45.510
you should at least win the Jin title.

00:16:45.510 --> 00:16:49.200
If you've got that kind of confidence, go ahead.

00:16:49.200 --> 00:16:54.000
Global opportunities will open for you,
and the experience won't hurt.

00:16:55.550 --> 00:16:57.180
I'll do it.

00:17:00.690 --> 00:17:02.860
I'll become Miss Korea Jin.

00:17:04.690 --> 00:17:07.230
[Minyeong Daily]

00:17:07.230 --> 00:17:10.340
[1989, 33rd Miss Korea Pageant,
Seoul Region Prelim Registration]

00:17:10.340 --> 00:17:12.400
We're in your hands.

00:17:12.400 --> 00:17:14.750
- Thank you.
- Sure.

00:17:16.740 --> 00:17:18.140
Jong Hui.

00:17:18.140 --> 00:17:23.640
Thank you so much for making
such a tough decision.

00:17:23.640 --> 00:17:29.510
How should I put it? It feels like
we've gained a whole army on our side.

00:17:29.510 --> 00:17:31.650
But tell me,

00:17:31.650 --> 00:17:35.600
how on earth did you persuade the Chairwoman?

00:17:35.600 --> 00:17:37.960
I begged her. I said I wanted to try it.

00:17:37.960 --> 00:17:43.620
Oh, my! Even the almighty Chairwoman
turns to mush for her daughter.

00:17:43.620 --> 00:17:46.620
That's so nice to see.

00:17:46.620 --> 00:17:49.500
Jong Hui, just trust me.

00:17:49.500 --> 00:17:51.540
There's nothing to worry about.

00:17:51.540 --> 00:17:53.370
Director...

00:17:57.360 --> 00:17:59.220
Hello!

00:18:00.850 --> 00:18:03.560
It's been a while, Director.
All has been well, right?

00:18:03.560 --> 00:18:04.960
I'm not sure.

00:18:04.960 --> 00:18:08.080
I doubt we're friendly enough to
be exchanging pleasantries.

00:18:08.080 --> 00:18:11.600
But giving the cold shoulder
is terribly tacky, isn't it?

00:18:13.300 --> 00:18:17.870
Anyway, where's Michelle's candidate?

00:18:21.100 --> 00:18:22.410
Jong Hui.

00:18:22.410 --> 00:18:25.220
What are you doing? Get in here.

00:18:36.330 --> 00:18:38.800
M-Ms. Ko!

00:18:38.800 --> 00:18:41.270
She looks a lot like Ms. Ko, doesn't she?

00:18:41.270 --> 00:18:44.800
No! That is Ms. Ko!

00:18:44.800 --> 00:18:46.240
Huh?

00:18:52.270 --> 00:18:54.070
Ms. Ko.

00:19:02.250 --> 00:19:04.510
Go ahead.

00:19:04.510 --> 00:19:06.650
You said you had something to tell me.

00:19:16.480 --> 00:19:22.940
I think it's only right that I tell you.

00:19:25.460 --> 00:19:30.420
Jong Hui, to be honest, Jae Pil and I...

00:19:30.420 --> 00:19:32.970
Did you decide to start dating or something?

00:19:36.640 --> 00:19:40.270
No need to make it sound so heavy.

00:19:40.270 --> 00:19:41.780
Congrats.

00:19:41.780 --> 00:19:44.740
In the end, Han Jae Pil's heart is yours.

00:19:48.280 --> 00:19:52.080
But your entering Miss Korea caught me off guard.

00:19:52.080 --> 00:19:55.150
It feels like I've been blindsided.

00:19:57.030 --> 00:20:01.060
Michelle's director took a liking to me.

00:20:01.920 --> 00:20:06.030
If I win Miss Korea Jin,
there's scholarship money.

00:20:06.030 --> 00:20:09.240
After a lot of thinking, I decided to try.

00:20:11.700 --> 00:20:13.900
The scholarship?

00:20:18.830 --> 00:20:20.800
Of course.

00:20:20.800 --> 00:20:24.010
Your dream is to attend college.

00:20:24.010 --> 00:20:27.800
Had I known you were Jullee's candidate,

00:20:28.840 --> 00:20:33.030
I might not have been able to decide.

00:20:33.030 --> 00:20:35.290
No.

00:20:35.290 --> 00:20:38.150
There's no need for that.

00:20:38.150 --> 00:20:41.800
Hearing you're competing only fires me up more.

00:20:43.120 --> 00:20:46.260
Give it all you've got.

00:20:46.260 --> 00:20:49.260
I'll give it my all as well.

00:20:52.470 --> 00:20:55.260
Let's play fair once again, Ko Yeong Rye.

00:20:59.040 --> 00:21:02.220
It won't be easy this time.

00:21:17.810 --> 00:21:20.730
One, two! Knees! Three.

00:21:20.730 --> 00:21:22.630
Four. Square your shoulders! One.

00:21:22.630 --> 00:21:26.000
Two. Brace your core! Three. Four.

00:21:26.000 --> 00:21:29.990
One, two, three, four.

00:21:29.990 --> 00:21:32.300
- One.
- Step forward. That's right.

00:21:32.300 --> 00:21:34.560
Keep your balance. Brace your core.

00:21:34.560 --> 00:21:36.380
Pose.

00:21:40.360 --> 00:21:41.670
That's right.

00:21:41.670 --> 00:21:45.610
Pose. Three, four! Go.

00:21:46.560 --> 00:21:49.090
Work it. Wear your confidence.

00:21:49.090 --> 00:21:52.120
Pose. Okay.

00:21:52.120 --> 00:21:54.360
Jong Hui is the best.

00:22:02.220 --> 00:22:06.560
Hello. I'm No. 34, Seo Jong Hui.

00:22:06.560 --> 00:22:09.610
Good job. Once you say your name,

00:22:09.610 --> 00:22:12.570
your smile should reach your eyes.

00:22:15.360 --> 00:22:17.470
One. One.

00:22:17.470 --> 00:22:20.840
One. One. One.

00:22:20.840 --> 00:22:22.820
Pose.

00:22:22.820 --> 00:22:25.760
One, two, three.

00:22:32.590 --> 00:22:35.770
We will now announce the winners of the

00:22:35.770 --> 00:22:39.300
Miss Seoul, who will advance to the
1989 Miss Korea pageant finals.

00:22:39.300 --> 00:22:42.440
Miss Seoul Mi*. No. 23, Cho Min Seon.
(Second runner-up)

00:22:42.440 --> 00:22:44.980
Seon*. No. 34, Seo Jong Hui.
(First runner-up)

00:22:44.980 --> 00:22:48.090
[1989 Miss Korea Pageant, Miss Seoul Prelim]
And Jin is No. 15, Ko Yeong Rye!

00:22:48.090 --> 00:22:49.380
[Yeongeun Market]

00:22:53.270 --> 00:22:55.440
Hope you sell a lot!

00:22:56.600 --> 00:22:58.500
- Gosh, Ms. Park!
- Hey.

00:22:58.500 --> 00:23:00.620
I heard the good news at your place.

00:23:00.620 --> 00:23:04.490
Good news? Please. It's nothing.

00:23:04.490 --> 00:23:07.160
Miss Korea, Seoul Jin. No big deal.

00:23:07.160 --> 00:23:09.430
Even if she makes the finals, we won't know.

00:23:09.430 --> 00:23:11.160
But still.

00:23:11.160 --> 00:23:14.470
But they do say that Miss Seoul Jin
has an advantage.

00:23:14.470 --> 00:23:16.090
My goodness!

00:23:17.720 --> 00:23:19.330
Damn it.

00:23:19.330 --> 00:23:20.850
The banner is crooked!

00:23:20.850 --> 00:23:22.150
[Congrats! Ko Yeong Rye, Miss Seoul Jin!]
How? Like this?

00:23:22.150 --> 00:23:24.200
A little higher!

00:23:24.200 --> 00:23:25.770
Higher? Here?

00:23:25.770 --> 00:23:27.390
What, Yeong Bae?

00:23:27.390 --> 00:23:29.100
- A little lower.
- Lower? Like this?

00:23:29.100 --> 00:23:30.470
Higher!

00:23:30.470 --> 00:23:32.010
Damn it!

00:23:32.010 --> 00:23:33.670
Are your eyes crooked?

00:23:33.670 --> 00:23:35.410
Why can't you line it up?

00:23:35.410 --> 00:23:37.610
Good, right? Look! Right here.

00:23:37.610 --> 00:23:40.060
That looks better.

00:23:40.870 --> 00:23:43.870
Mother, you should rein in that temper.

00:23:43.870 --> 00:23:46.920
You could soon be the mother of Miss Korea.

00:23:46.920 --> 00:23:51.540
I... I just wanted it to look nice.

00:23:51.540 --> 00:23:54.150
It looks perfect now.

00:23:55.350 --> 00:23:59.310
I still can't tell if this is a dream or not.

00:23:59.310 --> 00:24:03.790
What if Yeong Rye actually wins
Miss Korea Jin for real?

00:24:03.790 --> 00:24:06.560
Yeong Bae, Yeong Mi, what'll we do then, huh?

00:24:06.560 --> 00:24:08.130
That'd be amazing!

00:24:08.130 --> 00:24:10.850
I'll ask her to tour the TV station if she wins.

00:24:10.850 --> 00:24:12.260
I want to see Wan Sun* unni.
(Popular singer)

00:24:12.260 --> 00:24:15.610
Whoa, you already got the banner up.
Looks fantastic!

00:24:15.610 --> 00:24:16.660
- You're here?
- You came?

00:24:16.660 --> 00:24:18.720
- Hello.
- Hey.

00:24:18.720 --> 00:24:20.250
Yeong Rye isn't here yet?

00:24:20.250 --> 00:24:22.670
I came to congratulate her. I won't get
to see her once she starts training.

00:24:22.670 --> 00:24:25.830
She called and said she'll be a bit late.

00:24:25.830 --> 00:24:29.230
Sounds like there's a lot
to sort out with the director.

00:24:29.230 --> 00:24:33.580
Should we still throw a little celebration
without the star?

00:24:33.580 --> 00:24:34.950
It'll be my treat.

00:24:34.950 --> 00:24:38.040
You should eat out once in a while, too.

00:24:38.040 --> 00:24:40.290
Should we, then?

00:24:42.520 --> 00:24:44.200
All right! Why not!

00:24:44.200 --> 00:24:45.980
I might as well take advantage.

00:24:45.980 --> 00:24:47.890
Thanks to Yeong Rye, I'll close up shop.

00:24:47.890 --> 00:24:49.490
I'll let someone else do the cooking.

00:24:49.490 --> 00:24:50.810
- Let's go!
- Sure, sure.

00:24:50.810 --> 00:24:52.490
Please get ready.

00:24:54.210 --> 00:24:56.510
[Yeonseo University Hospital]

00:25:03.200 --> 00:25:04.630
Hello, this is the hospital.

00:25:04.630 --> 00:25:08.140
Is this Dr. Han Jae Pil by any chance?

00:25:10.250 --> 00:25:12.040
Well!

00:25:12.840 --> 00:25:14.140
Who could this be?

00:25:14.140 --> 00:25:16.710
Is it Miss Korea Seoul Jin?

00:25:16.710 --> 00:25:18.860
That's right.

00:25:18.860 --> 00:25:22.560
This is Ko Yeong Rye,
who somehow ended up Seoul Jin.

00:25:22.560 --> 00:25:26.720
What do you mean by "somehow"?
You won because you're worthy.

00:25:26.720 --> 00:25:30.180
I should congratulate you in person.

00:25:30.180 --> 00:25:32.240
But my co-resident on call

00:25:32.240 --> 00:25:35.470
had an emergency, and I'm covering for him.

00:25:35.470 --> 00:25:38.980
I really want to see you.

00:25:39.830 --> 00:25:41.250
Really?

00:25:42.140 --> 00:25:44.630
You want to see me that much?

00:25:44.630 --> 00:25:46.910
Of course I do.

00:25:47.730 --> 00:25:51.340
Once you start training, I won't get
to see you for a month.

00:25:51.340 --> 00:25:52.580
Yeah.

00:25:53.580 --> 00:25:57.570
If you want to see me that badly, then do it.

00:25:58.410 --> 00:26:02.450
Count to ten, then open the door.

00:26:04.980 --> 00:26:06.900
Gosh.

00:26:06.900 --> 00:26:08.300
No way-

00:26:18.830 --> 00:26:21.420
Hi, Dr. Han.

00:26:25.670 --> 00:26:27.610
How've you been?

00:26:31.260 --> 00:26:32.770
Wow.

00:26:34.070 --> 00:26:36.220
I'll dig in.

00:26:40.690 --> 00:26:43.860
It's my first time in here.

00:26:43.860 --> 00:26:47.400
Am I even allowed in here?

00:26:47.400 --> 00:26:51.180
Technically, no, but it's just me right now.

00:26:51.180 --> 00:26:52.990
Why? Are you uncomfortable?
Should we go elsewhere?

00:26:52.990 --> 00:26:54.470
No.

00:26:54.470 --> 00:26:56.430
You're on call.

00:26:56.430 --> 00:26:59.480
I'll watch you eat, and then I'll scoot.

00:27:02.540 --> 00:27:04.050
You eat, too.

00:27:05.080 --> 00:27:08.760
Miss Korea is great and all,
but you've gotten too thin.

00:27:08.760 --> 00:27:13.320
Ko Yeong Rye needs those plump cheeks to be cute.

00:27:14.670 --> 00:27:16.060
I can't.

00:27:16.060 --> 00:27:21.820
If I eat this and put on weight,
the director will kill me.

00:27:21.820 --> 00:27:24.710
Just one. One won't hurt.

00:27:24.710 --> 00:27:26.140
Here.

00:27:39.150 --> 00:27:42.800
Good girl. Look at you eat.

00:27:43.640 --> 00:27:44.770
It's good.

00:27:44.770 --> 00:27:46.340
Is it?

00:27:47.190 --> 00:27:48.820
Training camp is three weeks?

00:27:48.820 --> 00:27:50.290
Yeah.

00:27:51.920 --> 00:27:55.600
Gosh, three whole weeks
without this little hamster face.

00:27:55.600 --> 00:27:58.460
How am I supposed to survive?

00:27:58.460 --> 00:28:01.010
I don't think I can.

00:28:01.010 --> 00:28:02.840
That's too bad.

00:28:02.840 --> 00:28:07.640
Han Jae Pil is going to get sick from missing me.

00:28:11.080 --> 00:28:13.590
Better get my fill now.

00:28:13.590 --> 00:28:15.840
Ko Yeong Rye.

00:28:19.970 --> 00:28:22.870
Hey, didn't we finish the dumplings?

00:28:22.870 --> 00:28:25.410
I-I finished them.

00:28:26.170 --> 00:28:27.980
How did you pack them in here?

00:28:27.980 --> 00:28:30.580
Hey! Han Jae Pil.

00:28:30.580 --> 00:28:32.100
All right. All right.

00:28:32.100 --> 00:28:33.770
All right.

00:28:38.100 --> 00:28:40.280
[Yeongeun Market]

00:28:40.280 --> 00:28:42.060
Home already.

00:28:43.060 --> 00:28:46.270
Was your house always this close to the bus stop?

00:28:46.270 --> 00:28:49.850
I know. It's too close.

00:28:51.230 --> 00:28:53.980
Let's go. I'll take you home.

00:28:53.980 --> 00:28:55.710
No way.

00:28:55.710 --> 00:28:58.970
Your training starts tomorrow.
You need to go home and pack.

00:28:58.970 --> 00:29:00.840
You said you'll get dropped
if you can't make it by nine.

00:29:00.840 --> 00:29:03.740
No. It's okay. I can wake up on time.

00:29:03.740 --> 00:29:05.270
Let's go.

00:29:05.270 --> 00:29:07.260
- Gosh.
- Let's go.

00:29:07.260 --> 00:29:09.870
We really shouldn't.

00:29:15.890 --> 00:29:18.050
Did we just teleport here?

00:29:18.920 --> 00:29:21.010
We're at my place already?

00:29:21.010 --> 00:29:24.350
We walked as slowly as possible, too.

00:29:24.350 --> 00:29:26.390
This can't be.

00:29:28.170 --> 00:29:30.490
This won't do. I'll take you back home.

00:29:30.490 --> 00:29:32.060
- Let's go.
- What are you saying?

00:29:32.060 --> 00:29:34.910
I can just take a taxi. You have work tomorrow.

00:29:34.910 --> 00:29:36.990
No! Riding the taxi alone is dangerous.

00:29:36.990 --> 00:29:39.440
Let's go. Come on.

00:29:45.350 --> 00:29:47.260
Go inside for real.

00:29:47.260 --> 00:29:50.080
It's late. Start packing.

00:29:51.660 --> 00:29:54.100
You go first. I'll go in after you leave.

00:29:54.100 --> 00:29:57.300
- I live right around the corner.
- It's okay.

00:29:57.300 --> 00:30:00.500
I'll go after you go in. Get inside.

00:30:03.170 --> 00:30:09.330
You won't forget my face just because
you won't see me for a month, right?

00:30:10.180 --> 00:30:14.410
Just in case, let me take a good look at you.

00:30:19.560 --> 00:30:21.340
What?

00:30:21.340 --> 00:30:23.810
Without any warning!

00:30:28.670 --> 00:30:31.890
Gosh, you're in for it.

00:30:31.890 --> 00:30:33.130
Come here.

00:30:33.130 --> 00:30:34.660
Hey!

00:31:08.400 --> 00:31:14.920
So, when did it turn into that kind
of relationship between you and Jae Pil?

00:31:14.920 --> 00:31:18.230
Stop killing us with the suspense, girl.

00:31:18.230 --> 00:31:24.790
Since when did you two start doing this
and that and end up like that?

00:31:24.790 --> 00:31:27.340
Can't you just tell us that much?

00:31:28.690 --> 00:31:30.720
Whatever! Leave her be.

00:31:30.720 --> 00:31:33.220
We've been friends long enough.

00:31:33.220 --> 00:31:36.680
She'll tell us when it's time
to print the wedding invites.

00:31:36.680 --> 00:31:40.590
Or maybe when there's a baby, she'll let us know.

00:31:40.590 --> 00:31:43.710
- Whatever.
- We'll see you when our niece is born.

00:31:43.710 --> 00:31:46.640
I-It was then.

00:31:47.960 --> 00:31:50.980
When I went to the beauty seminar in Dongincheon.

00:31:50.980 --> 00:31:52.890
- Huh? The beauty seminar?
- Yeah.

00:31:52.890 --> 00:31:54.430
Goodness! On that day-

00:31:54.430 --> 00:31:56.440
What did I say back then, huh?

00:31:56.440 --> 00:32:00.080
I told you she'd been suspicious ever
since her first day at Michelle.

00:32:00.080 --> 00:32:03.650
Okay, that's enough. Go now.
I need to finish packing.

00:32:03.650 --> 00:32:06.030
Who made the first move?

00:32:06.030 --> 00:32:07.980
- Who confessed first?
- Tell us.

00:32:07.980 --> 00:32:10.120
Was it you?

00:32:10.120 --> 00:32:12.520
No one was first.

00:32:12.520 --> 00:32:14.880
It just happened.

00:32:16.290 --> 00:32:18.270
And kissing?

00:32:19.290 --> 00:32:21.380
Did you kiss?

00:32:21.380 --> 00:32:26.480
And not those peck-peck
little kiddie kisses like earlier.

00:32:26.480 --> 00:32:28.280
We did.

00:32:30.950 --> 00:32:33.360
Get out now! I have to pack.

00:32:33.360 --> 00:32:34.840
Where did you kiss?

00:32:34.840 --> 00:32:38.350
- It's important!
- Tell us!

00:32:46.590 --> 00:32:49.560
[1989 Miss Korea Pageant,
Contestant Training Camp]

00:33:03.900 --> 00:33:05.770
- Be careful.
- I'm sorry.

00:33:05.770 --> 00:33:08.130
I'm sorry. So sorry.

00:33:09.050 --> 00:33:11.560
That's her, right? Seoul Jin.

00:33:11.560 --> 00:33:15.490
- You made it.
- She doesn't exactly scream Jin material.

00:33:15.490 --> 00:33:18.950
Still, Seoul Jin is the favorite
almost every year.

00:33:18.950 --> 00:33:21.320
- But I heard Seoul Seon is no pushover.
- Really?

00:33:21.320 --> 00:33:26.140
I thought I'd be late, so I ran like crazy.

00:33:26.140 --> 00:33:29.930
Testing, testing. Can everyone hear me?

00:33:29.930 --> 00:33:31.530
Yes!

00:33:32.530 --> 00:33:38.560
I'm the finals committee member
who'll be running your programs

00:33:38.560 --> 00:33:42.600
and supervising you throughout the training camp.

00:33:42.600 --> 00:33:45.740
My name is Lee Byeong Hoon.

00:33:49.520 --> 00:33:53.340
Before we assign two-person rooms,

00:33:53.340 --> 00:33:59.210
we should first pick a class rep
to act as the leader.

00:33:59.210 --> 00:34:02.100
Given the time and for convenience,

00:34:02.100 --> 00:34:05.300
- we'll have Miss Seoul Jin-
- I'll do it!

00:34:06.940 --> 00:34:09.880
I'd like to try being a class rep.

00:34:11.100 --> 00:34:15.290
I never got to be class rep in school.
It's my lifelong regret.

00:34:15.290 --> 00:34:18.600
All right then, class rep is...

00:34:18.600 --> 00:34:20.460
No. 10, Miss Seoul Seon.

00:34:20.460 --> 00:34:23.770
Okay. Class rep is Seoul Seon.

00:34:23.770 --> 00:34:28.500
If you've got suggestions or issues,
bring them to No. 10.

00:34:28.500 --> 00:34:30.690
I'll do my best!

00:34:33.020 --> 00:34:36.080
Then, shall we pick the numbers of fate

00:34:36.080 --> 00:34:39.360
that will decide your room assignments?

00:34:42.810 --> 00:34:44.640
[Room 314]

00:34:51.580 --> 00:34:52.860
[Room 314]

00:34:59.840 --> 00:35:01.410
[Room 314]

00:35:07.600 --> 00:35:09.640
[Room 314]

00:35:13.350 --> 00:35:18.420
[Ko Yeong Rye / Seo Jong Hui]

00:35:22.680 --> 00:35:24.790
The room is quite small.

00:35:24.790 --> 00:35:27.840
Fortunately, there's a bathroom.

00:35:27.840 --> 00:35:30.530
It's still way bigger than my room.

00:35:30.530 --> 00:35:32.560
Which bed do you want?

00:35:32.560 --> 00:35:34.470
You pick.

00:35:34.470 --> 00:35:37.200
I don't know. Do you want the inside?

00:35:37.200 --> 00:35:41.100
The hall side might be noisy.
You're a light sleeper.

00:35:42.870 --> 00:35:46.130
We know too much about each other.

00:35:46.130 --> 00:35:48.340
I'll take the inside then.

00:35:51.040 --> 00:35:53.860
Still, isn't it wild?

00:35:53.860 --> 00:35:58.860
Out of all those girls, how did we
end up drawing the same number?

00:35:58.860 --> 00:36:01.180
Exactly.

00:36:01.180 --> 00:36:04.080
I don't know if we should call it fate...

00:36:05.230 --> 00:36:07.530
or destiny.

00:36:11.770 --> 00:36:14.110
I'm going to check out next door.

00:36:14.110 --> 00:36:16.630
Class rep should make friends fast.

00:36:16.630 --> 00:36:19.040
Okay, go ahead.

00:36:20.020 --> 00:36:22.790
I'm aiming for the Friendship Award.

00:36:22.790 --> 00:36:25.440
I hear it earns you bonus points.

00:36:35.670 --> 00:36:36.720
Uncle!

00:36:36.720 --> 00:36:39.100
Yes, Su Jin.

00:36:39.100 --> 00:36:40.990
Did you sleep well?

00:36:45.360 --> 00:36:46.550
What's going on this morning?

00:36:46.550 --> 00:36:48.580
I'm sorry,

00:36:48.580 --> 00:36:52.140
but could you watch Su Jin for a few hours?

00:36:52.140 --> 00:36:54.400
The kindergarten is closed today.

00:36:54.400 --> 00:36:56.570
After Mother and Ho Suk are done with deliveries,

00:36:56.570 --> 00:36:59.520
they will be swamped getting ready
for a group reservation.

00:36:59.520 --> 00:37:01.440
Sure, all right.

00:37:01.440 --> 00:37:05.650
She can hang out with me.
Don't worry and get to work.

00:37:05.650 --> 00:37:07.070
I'm really sorry.

00:37:07.070 --> 00:37:09.200
I'll make it up to you.

00:37:09.200 --> 00:37:10.940
You always say that.

00:37:10.940 --> 00:37:13.430
No need to repay kindness.

00:37:13.430 --> 00:37:15.510
Wait a minute.

00:37:15.510 --> 00:37:17.580
If you must...

00:37:21.050 --> 00:37:23.280
buy me a meal sometime.

00:37:24.590 --> 00:37:25.970
A meal?

00:37:27.570 --> 00:37:29.990
- Yes, a meal.
- A meal.

00:37:29.990 --> 00:37:35.530
Sure, I can buy a meal, but…

00:37:37.120 --> 00:37:39.240
Got it. I'll buy you a meal.

00:37:39.240 --> 00:37:40.530
Okay.

00:37:41.400 --> 00:37:44.060
Su Jin, be good and listen to Uncle, okay?

00:37:44.060 --> 00:37:46.590
Auntie Ho Suk will come later.

00:37:47.380 --> 00:37:49.330
- Mommy is off!
- Say bye to mommy.

00:37:49.330 --> 00:37:51.900
Bye, Mommy.

00:37:52.770 --> 00:37:54.130
- Get going.
- Thank you.

00:37:54.130 --> 00:37:55.660
Sure.

00:37:56.790 --> 00:38:00.010
Gosh, my little Su Jin.

00:38:00.010 --> 00:38:02.890
Long time no date with Uncle.

00:38:02.890 --> 00:38:04.870
What should we do?

00:38:04.870 --> 00:38:06.660
I want to fly a kite.

00:38:06.660 --> 00:38:08.640
A kite? Sure!

00:38:08.640 --> 00:38:11.860
Shall we go buy one at the stationery store?

00:38:13.280 --> 00:38:15.910
Su Jin.

00:38:16.940 --> 00:38:19.930
Aigoo, aigoo.

00:38:20.750 --> 00:38:22.360
Aigoo...

00:38:23.990 --> 00:38:26.240
Have you been well?

00:38:26.240 --> 00:38:29.740
I wasn't because I missed you so much.

00:38:29.740 --> 00:38:31.280
Hello.

00:38:31.280 --> 00:38:33.680
Sure, sure.

00:38:38.180 --> 00:38:41.290
Why is my Su Jin with you again?

00:38:43.170 --> 00:38:45.750
I'm just watching her for a bit.

00:38:46.600 --> 00:38:50.100
Jeong Bun went to work,
and Mother and Ho Suk are busy.

00:38:50.100 --> 00:38:53.460
It's fine. I'll play with her.
You go mind your business.

00:38:53.460 --> 00:38:55.470
Let's go, Su Jin.

00:38:55.470 --> 00:38:57.430
What do you want?

00:38:57.430 --> 00:39:01.290
Daddy- no, Ahjussi will buy you a pretty dress.

00:39:09.740 --> 00:39:11.300
Let's see.

00:39:12.290 --> 00:39:14.120
The clothes don't do you justice.

00:39:14.120 --> 00:39:17.500
Ma'am, don't you have any princess-style dresses?

00:39:17.500 --> 00:39:21.590
The kind that girls like. With lots
of lace and frills. Sha-la-la.

00:39:21.590 --> 00:39:22.870
Something pink.

00:39:22.870 --> 00:39:25.140
Of course, we do.

00:39:26.140 --> 00:39:28.860
There are more back there?

00:39:28.860 --> 00:39:32.010
How about this? Very pink-pink.

00:39:32.010 --> 00:39:34.930
It's pink, sure. But kind of an ugly pink.

00:39:34.930 --> 00:39:36.970
Do you have a prettier pink?

00:39:36.970 --> 00:39:38.150
We have this one, too.

00:39:38.150 --> 00:39:39.960
Should I take her to a department store?

00:39:39.960 --> 00:39:43.060
I want to dress her up and
get her something tasty.

00:39:44.090 --> 00:39:46.210
Oh, this one is pretty!

00:39:47.000 --> 00:39:48.710
This is pretty.

00:39:48.710 --> 00:39:50.620
Do you have this dress one size bigger?

00:39:50.620 --> 00:39:52.690
- I do.
- This is perfect.

00:39:52.690 --> 00:39:55.070
Right, Su Jin? This is pretty-

00:39:56.600 --> 00:39:58.250
Su Jin?

00:39:59.910 --> 00:40:01.450
Su Jin.

00:40:01.450 --> 00:40:04.930
Where did she go? Where's Su Jin... Su Jin.

00:40:06.230 --> 00:40:07.960
Su Jin!

00:40:07.960 --> 00:40:10.120
Su Jin!

00:40:10.120 --> 00:40:12.500
- Su Jin!
- Su Jin!

00:40:12.500 --> 00:40:14.660
- Su Jin!
- Did you find her?

00:40:14.660 --> 00:40:16.230
No. Where does she usually-

00:40:16.230 --> 00:40:17.420
She's not on this side!

00:40:17.420 --> 00:40:20.320
We checked everywhere she might go.

00:40:20.320 --> 00:40:22.410
None of the market folks has seen her.

00:40:22.410 --> 00:40:26.210
Where could that little thing have gone?

00:40:26.210 --> 00:40:28.960
Gosh, my heart is trembling.

00:40:28.960 --> 00:40:30.820
What should we do?

