The show is over.

00:49:29.090 --> 00:49:31.950
Is there anything good on?

00:49:34.770 --> 00:49:39.600
The 40 finalists of the 1989,
33rd Miss Korea Pageant

00:49:39.600 --> 00:49:43.170
have begun their training camp.

00:49:43.170 --> 00:49:46.870
Selected through fierce regional
prelims, the contestants

00:49:46.870 --> 00:49:49.560
will undergo programs and
community service to cultivate

00:49:49.560 --> 00:49:54.380
- My sister. T-That's my sister.
- the qualities expected of Miss Korea.

00:49:54.380 --> 00:49:57.400
Starting with the welcome ceremony last week,

00:49:57.400 --> 00:50:00.030
they've visited an orphanage in Hanbong-dong...

00:50:00.030 --> 00:50:01.380
She's your sister?

00:50:01.380 --> 00:50:03.760
Yes! That's my little sister.

00:50:03.760 --> 00:50:07.490
Wow, that bitch. Talk about talent.

00:50:07.490 --> 00:50:10.080
I went to her work right
after I got out of prison,

00:50:10.080 --> 00:50:11.790
but she wasn't there.

00:50:11.790 --> 00:50:13.340
And how did she?

00:50:13.340 --> 00:50:15.960
Wow, shocking, man!

00:50:15.960 --> 00:50:18.550
Where she worked?

00:50:18.550 --> 00:50:20.050
Cheongah Transportation?

00:50:20.050 --> 00:50:22.800
Wait, how do you know that?

00:50:22.800 --> 00:50:24.450
Did you work there?

00:50:24.450 --> 00:50:27.410
This is a meaningful encounter
for these 40 beauties...

00:50:27.410 --> 00:50:32.740
So, Seo Jong Hui, the bus attendant
from Cheongah Transportation

00:50:32.740 --> 00:50:34.700
is your sister?

00:50:34.700 --> 00:50:37.820
That's what I'm telling you.

00:50:37.820 --> 00:50:40.760
There's something there.

00:50:40.760 --> 00:50:43.180
She's got backing, for sure.

00:50:44.180 --> 00:50:47.550
If I play this right, I might snag
something out of it.

00:50:47.550 --> 00:50:49.460
Don't you think so, Hyungnim?

00:50:53.410 --> 00:50:56.130
Everyone, can you hear me?

00:50:56.130 --> 00:50:58.120
Yes!

00:50:58.120 --> 00:51:02.950
Normally, outings aren't allowed
during training camp.

00:51:02.950 --> 00:51:07.580
But thanks to how well this cohort has kept up

00:51:07.580 --> 00:51:10.850
with the heavy schedule and rehearsals,

00:51:10.850 --> 00:51:13.660
we wrapped up early.

00:51:13.660 --> 00:51:16.650
With special permission
from the Association President,

00:51:16.650 --> 00:51:21.540
you're getting a half-day reward outing.

00:51:24.630 --> 00:51:26.630
Curfew is 9 p.m.

00:51:26.630 --> 00:51:29.000
Anyone back after nine gets demerits,

00:51:29.000 --> 00:51:31.810
so be on time. No exceptions.

00:51:31.810 --> 00:51:33.930
Yes, sir!

00:51:34.920 --> 00:51:37.530
Is Auntie Yeong Rye coming? Do you see her?

00:51:37.530 --> 00:51:38.630
No.

00:51:38.630 --> 00:51:40.230
I don't see her yet.

00:51:40.230 --> 00:51:42.300
Is she here yet? Do you see her?

00:51:42.300 --> 00:51:45.180
No. I don't see a hair on her head.

00:51:45.180 --> 00:51:48.820
It's only been two weeks, but I miss her to death.

00:51:48.820 --> 00:51:51.890
She'll come eventually.

00:51:51.890 --> 00:51:55.120
Stop making a fuss and just wait.

00:51:56.050 --> 00:51:57.550
Hello.

00:51:57.550 --> 00:51:59.190
Oh, she's here!

00:51:59.190 --> 00:52:00.320
Yeong Rye!

00:52:00.320 --> 00:52:02.320
Unni!

00:52:02.320 --> 00:52:03.910
What took you so long?

00:52:03.910 --> 00:52:05.240
Have you been well?

00:52:05.240 --> 00:52:07.420
Is the food to your liking?

00:52:07.420 --> 00:52:09.300
Do they skimp on the food?

00:52:09.300 --> 00:52:11.300
You look so thin.

00:52:11.300 --> 00:52:13.870
Miss Korea is good and all,
but you need to eat well.

00:52:13.870 --> 00:52:18.470
I'm fine, Mom. I've been eating and living well.

00:52:18.470 --> 00:52:21.240
Su Jin! How have you been?

00:52:21.240 --> 00:52:23.890
- She's been good.
- You've been well?

00:52:29.250 --> 00:52:31.930
Why did you prepare so much, Mom?

00:52:31.930 --> 00:52:33.670
I shouldn't gain weight.

00:52:33.670 --> 00:52:35.470
It's nothing much.

00:52:35.470 --> 00:52:38.300
I just made some braised galbi,
stir-fried bulgogi,

00:52:38.300 --> 00:52:41.630
cooked your favorite soybean paste stew,
mixed some japchae,

00:52:41.630 --> 00:52:43.560
tossed a few greens, and fried a few pancakes.

00:52:43.560 --> 00:52:46.320
What did I do? There's nothing much.

00:52:46.320 --> 00:52:47.770
Unbelievable.

00:52:47.770 --> 00:52:50.720
I give you credit for having a generous hand.

00:52:50.720 --> 00:52:53.240
- Let's eat.
- Yeah, let's.

00:52:53.240 --> 00:52:55.970
- Thank you for the food!
- Thank you for the food.

00:52:55.970 --> 00:52:57.770
Yeong Rye, try the japchae.

00:52:57.770 --> 00:53:00.600
It's insanely good.

00:53:00.600 --> 00:53:03.840
Have some braised galbi, too.

00:53:03.840 --> 00:53:09.100
The seasoning is nice and savory.
It's dancing in my mouth.

00:53:09.100 --> 00:53:12.000
And your favorite bean sprouts.

00:53:12.000 --> 00:53:13.970
Pumpkin pancake, too.

00:53:13.970 --> 00:53:15.500
Thanks.

00:53:15.500 --> 00:53:17.460
Me, too. I want to give you, too.

00:53:17.460 --> 00:53:18.810
What will you give me?

00:53:18.810 --> 00:53:20.840
I'll give you anchovies.

00:53:20.840 --> 00:53:25.720
Aigoo, aigoo! I should try
Su Jin's anchovies first.

00:53:26.970 --> 00:53:29.220
It's so good! Yummy!

00:53:29.220 --> 00:53:30.880
Try this, too.

00:53:30.880 --> 00:53:33.280
Wait, when is Jae Pil coming?

00:53:33.280 --> 00:53:34.620
That's right.

00:53:34.620 --> 00:53:39.230
Mr. Ma said he'll come over
after his seminar or whatever ends.

00:53:39.230 --> 00:53:41.080
He'll get here when he gets here.

00:53:41.080 --> 00:53:43.890
Let's eat first.

00:53:45.740 --> 00:53:47.570
It's good.

00:53:47.570 --> 00:53:50.290
Gosh, look at our Miss Korea.

00:53:50.290 --> 00:53:52.280
You're so pretty!

00:53:52.280 --> 00:53:53.640
Have you been well?

00:53:53.640 --> 00:53:55.070
You're the same, Mr. Ma.

00:53:55.070 --> 00:53:56.370
Uncle!

00:53:56.370 --> 00:53:58.250
Aigoo, our Su Jin.

00:53:58.250 --> 00:54:00.910
Are you enjoying your meal?

00:54:00.910 --> 00:54:02.300
Have a seat there.

00:54:02.300 --> 00:54:03.950
- Sure, Mother.
- Do you have a spoon?

00:54:03.950 --> 00:54:04.980
I don't.

00:54:04.980 --> 00:54:07.520
Cardiopulmonary resuscitation can be divided into

00:54:07.520 --> 00:54:09.970
basic life support and advanced life support.

00:54:09.970 --> 00:54:12.560
Into two levels.

00:54:12.560 --> 00:54:15.240
What's the difference?

00:54:15.240 --> 00:54:18.530
It's the quality of resuscitation.

00:54:18.530 --> 00:54:21.200
Advanced life support is performed professionally

00:54:21.200 --> 00:54:26.000
by medical personnel such
as 119 paramedics and doctors.

00:54:26.000 --> 00:54:34.400
So, what can be included in advanced life support?

00:54:34.400 --> 00:54:37.800
You, the fidgeting intern.

00:54:37.800 --> 00:54:41.300
Yes, you. Answer the question.

00:54:43.480 --> 00:54:44.820
In addition to chest compressions,

00:54:44.820 --> 00:54:47.660
they can perform intubation or
use drugs like epinephrine

00:54:47.660 --> 00:54:50.840
and treat by observing the patient's condition.

00:54:50.840 --> 00:54:54.900
I guess you were concentrating.

00:54:54.900 --> 00:54:58.180
With the increase in emergency patients
from traffic accidents and so on,

00:54:58.180 --> 00:55:01.520
emergency treatments like CPR
have become very important.

00:55:01.520 --> 00:55:06.200
Although we're running out of time,

00:55:06.200 --> 00:55:09.500
you must get some practice,
so please come forward.

00:55:09.500 --> 00:55:13.400
We don't have many mannequins,
so come starting from the front.

00:55:16.070 --> 00:55:17.160
Welcome.

00:55:17.160 --> 00:55:18.310
Have you been well?

00:55:18.310 --> 00:55:19.910
- Yes.
- Where's Mom?

00:55:19.910 --> 00:55:21.490
She just called.

00:55:21.490 --> 00:55:24.230
She was out of town and only just
got back to the office.

00:55:24.230 --> 00:55:26.210
She'll be home after giving some urgent approvals

00:55:26.210 --> 00:55:28.230
and asked me to have dinner ready.

00:55:28.230 --> 00:55:29.290
Are you hungry?

00:55:29.290 --> 00:55:31.440
No, I'm okay. You can start preparing.

00:55:31.440 --> 00:55:33.210
Should I take the flowers?

00:55:33.210 --> 00:55:35.440
I'll give it to her personally.

00:55:46.160 --> 00:55:48.750
Let's reschedule the board item.

00:55:48.750 --> 00:55:51.120
I need more time to review.

00:55:51.120 --> 00:55:52.310
Yes, ma'am.

00:55:52.310 --> 00:55:53.880
I have to go. My daughter is waiting.

00:55:53.880 --> 00:55:55.840
Yes, of course.

00:56:04.050 --> 00:56:06.930
Chairwoman, a man in the lobby says
he's Seo Jong Hui's brother.

00:56:06.930 --> 00:56:08.840
He's asking to see you.

00:56:09.710 --> 00:56:11.740
All right. Send him up.

00:56:19.000 --> 00:56:21.070
See?

00:56:21.070 --> 00:56:24.890
I told you dropping "Seo Jong Hui's brother"
would get us in.

00:56:24.890 --> 00:56:27.150
I cleared the path like we agreed,

00:56:27.150 --> 00:56:29.690
so you handle the rest.

00:56:29.690 --> 00:56:34.680
I spook easily around big shots like
chairmen and directors.

00:56:35.940 --> 00:56:38.960
And remember, we split it 50-50.

00:56:38.960 --> 00:56:41.370
Don't worry about me.

00:56:41.370 --> 00:56:44.100
Just keep your end of the bargain.

00:56:46.670 --> 00:56:48.440
All right.

00:56:49.440 --> 00:56:53.850
This is proof that I'm Seo Jong Hui's
biological brother.

00:56:53.850 --> 00:56:55.540
[Household Registration Certificate]

00:56:55.540 --> 00:57:00.220
And this is the insurance policy
our parents took out.

00:57:00.220 --> 00:57:01.330
[Insurance Certificate]

00:57:03.050 --> 00:57:05.310
After our parents passed away,

00:57:05.310 --> 00:57:10.430
that bitch collected the entire payout.

00:57:10.430 --> 00:57:13.020
That's the type of bitch she is.

00:57:13.020 --> 00:57:16.480
Did you know that before you adopted her?

00:57:19.420 --> 00:57:24.250
You think I'd adopt her
without checking that much?

00:57:24.250 --> 00:57:25.500
What?

00:57:25.500 --> 00:57:30.870
I heard there was a brother who seized
the payout and gambled it away.

00:57:30.870 --> 00:57:33.310
You're lower-class than I expected.

00:57:34.810 --> 00:57:38.750
You really think her background
is leverage over me?

00:57:40.220 --> 00:57:41.710
Then,

00:57:43.410 --> 00:57:47.640
if Seo Jong Hui were a criminal
who committed attempted murder...

00:57:52.390 --> 00:57:54.920
would that be a threat?

00:57:58.470 --> 00:58:01.510
That bitch stabbed me with a fountain pen.

00:58:01.510 --> 00:58:04.750
Seven years ago at the Cheongah
Transportation office.

00:58:04.750 --> 00:58:09.470
Because of that incident, I became
disabled and can't use my shoulder.

00:58:13.730 --> 00:58:16.130
If I leak this to the press...

00:58:18.270 --> 00:58:21.710
it'll get in the way of her becoming Miss Korea.

00:58:49.340 --> 00:58:53.210
Even if that's true, I won't negotiate.

00:58:53.210 --> 00:58:55.990
I know how people like you work.

00:58:55.990 --> 00:58:59.280
Once becomes twice, and the demands are endless.

00:59:00.440 --> 00:59:02.720
If you want to expose it, then go ahead.

00:59:02.720 --> 00:59:05.040
I'll deal with it my way.

00:59:05.040 --> 00:59:06.830
So, are we done here?

00:59:06.830 --> 00:59:08.800
Take care on your way back.

00:59:34.450 --> 00:59:38.740
They said she left the office. That's strange.

00:59:38.740 --> 00:59:41.500
You should go ahead and eat.
You must be hungry.

00:59:41.500 --> 00:59:43.060
I'll reheat the steak again.

00:59:43.060 --> 00:59:45.430
No, it's fine.

00:59:45.430 --> 00:59:48.000
I don't think there's enough time to eat.

00:59:54.560 --> 00:59:56.940
Hyungnim. Hold on.

00:59:56.940 --> 00:59:58.820
Hold on, Hyungnim.

00:59:58.820 --> 01:00:00.560
Hyungnim!

01:00:02.190 --> 01:00:04.750
Is it true?

01:00:04.750 --> 01:00:08.790
That Jong Yeon- No.
That Jong Hui stabbed you?

01:00:08.790 --> 01:00:10.420
You never told me that.

01:00:10.420 --> 01:00:14.440
There's only one reason I played along with you.

01:00:14.440 --> 01:00:17.320
I thought it'd be convenient to get to her.

01:00:17.320 --> 01:00:22.000
But now that it's come to this,
let's go our separate ways.

01:00:22.000 --> 01:00:24.480
I'll never give up.

01:00:29.800 --> 01:00:31.880
Shit.

01:00:31.880 --> 01:00:35.280
What the hell did that bitch do?

01:00:36.290 --> 01:00:39.260
This puts me in a difficult position.

01:00:42.440 --> 01:00:44.080
Shit.

01:01:14.210 --> 01:01:16.290
This is Hyeonseong Daily, right?

01:01:18.010 --> 01:01:25.570
I have a tip about this year's
Miss Korea candidate.

01:01:35.990 --> 01:01:37.700
Yeong Rye!

01:01:43.890 --> 01:01:45.620
Yeong Rye!

01:01:47.530 --> 01:01:49.190
Ko Yeong Rye!

01:01:51.040 --> 01:01:53.110
Han Jae Pil?

01:01:53.110 --> 01:01:55.420
Umbrella. Get in here.

01:01:56.400 --> 01:01:58.160
Jae Pil.

01:01:58.160 --> 01:02:01.670
I'm sorry. The seminar ended too late.

01:02:01.670 --> 01:02:03.320
I called your house,

01:02:03.320 --> 01:02:06.610
but they said you left already,
so I caught a taxi-

01:02:15.990 --> 01:02:18.570
I missed you so much.

01:02:18.570 --> 01:02:21.120
I missed you so much, Ko Yeong Rye.

01:02:22.610 --> 01:02:24.250
Me, too.

01:02:24.250 --> 01:02:27.910
I missed you so much, too, Han Jae Pil.

01:02:32.920 --> 01:02:37.020
Why didn't you use the umbrella when it's raining?

01:02:38.210 --> 01:02:40.400
I was in a hurry.

01:02:42.940 --> 01:02:47.010
You got even more handsome
while I hadn't seen you, Dr. Han Jae Pil.

01:02:47.010 --> 01:02:51.430
Hardly. You kept me up at night
because I missed you.

01:02:53.060 --> 01:02:54.520
Here.

01:02:54.520 --> 01:02:56.420
What's this?

01:02:59.320 --> 01:03:00.810
It's delicious.

01:03:00.810 --> 01:03:02.510
- It's good?
- Yeah.

01:03:03.740 --> 01:03:06.230
I had two bowls of rice,

01:03:06.230 --> 01:03:08.850
but I still have room for this.

01:03:08.850 --> 01:03:13.310
I'm going to return from this outing as a pig.

01:03:13.310 --> 01:03:15.430
Pig is fine,

01:03:15.430 --> 01:03:16.800
and hamster is fine.

01:03:16.800 --> 01:03:19.820
Miss Korea or not, it's okay.

01:03:19.820 --> 01:03:22.030
I'm fine as long as it's Ko Yeong Rye.

01:03:22.030 --> 01:03:28.040
Han Jae Pil, you've gotten kind
of cheesy while I was gone.

01:03:28.040 --> 01:03:33.200
Are you taking classes at an
academy to learn these lines?

01:03:33.200 --> 01:03:35.080
Hey, stop that.

01:03:35.080 --> 01:03:36.990
- Don't.
- Come on.

01:03:39.020 --> 01:03:40.270
Hey!

01:03:40.270 --> 01:03:41.950
All right.

01:03:41.950 --> 01:03:43.210
Want some, too?

01:03:43.210 --> 01:03:44.610
Yeah, I do.

01:03:44.610 --> 01:03:46.940
Watching you eat is making me hungry.

01:03:46.940 --> 01:03:48.720
Here. Say, ah.

01:04:06.120 --> 01:04:07.600
Mom!

01:04:07.600 --> 01:04:10.100
You came straight here?

01:04:10.100 --> 01:04:14.050
I was actually waiting for you at home-

01:04:17.010 --> 01:04:21.570
Your brother and that bus company
manager came to see me.

01:04:21.570 --> 01:04:23.900
He said you nearly killed him.

01:04:23.900 --> 01:04:26.660
They're threatening to tip off the press
for attempted murder.

01:04:26.660 --> 01:04:29.800
Why should I be subjected to threats
from bottom-feeders like that?

01:04:29.800 --> 01:04:33.270
Just how far down did you sink?

01:04:44.770 --> 01:04:49.090
I'll handle this quietly on my end.

01:04:49.090 --> 01:04:54.010
In return, you do whatever it takes to win Jin.

01:04:54.010 --> 01:04:57.380
Otherwise, the humiliation I just
swallowed won't be worth it.

01:05:45.170 --> 01:05:47.270
- Jong Hui.
- Don't.

01:05:51.780 --> 01:05:54.660
- Jong Hui.
- Let go!

01:06:05.290 --> 01:06:07.520
What's wrong?

01:06:08.740 --> 01:06:11.700
What on earth happened?

01:06:11.700 --> 01:06:18.100
What happened that your mom came
all the way here and laid a hand on you?

01:06:21.780 --> 01:06:23.410
This isn't...

01:06:25.240 --> 01:06:27.410
the first time, is it?

01:06:29.650 --> 01:06:31.040
Huh?

01:06:33.190 --> 01:06:35.710
She loves you when it suits her,

01:06:35.710 --> 01:06:38.920
but she yells and hits when it doesn't.

01:06:38.920 --> 01:06:41.990
Is that what it's like being her daughter?

01:06:41.990 --> 01:06:43.530
Is it?

01:06:49.110 --> 01:06:51.590
Why live like that?

01:06:52.790 --> 01:06:54.720
Why?

01:06:55.840 --> 01:06:57.900
Even if you're a rich family's daughter,

01:06:57.900 --> 01:07:01.880
this isn't happiness. Right?

01:07:03.140 --> 01:07:07.030
Why force yourself to live there like that?

01:07:07.030 --> 01:07:09.390
That's not like Seo Jong Hui.

01:07:11.450 --> 01:07:13.740
Why do I live like this?

01:07:17.130 --> 01:07:19.050
You really don't know?

01:07:22.010 --> 01:07:24.320
It's because of you.

01:07:30.390 --> 01:07:34.020
At Cheongah Transportation, I was so happy.

01:07:35.980 --> 01:07:38.550
On off-days, I went to your place,

01:07:38.550 --> 01:07:42.680
snuck ramen with Jeong Bun and Ho Suk.

01:07:43.710 --> 01:07:46.360
For the first time in my life, I felt happy there.

01:07:46.360 --> 01:07:49.660
Why do you think I left there?

01:07:49.660 --> 01:07:51.530
Why do you think...

01:07:53.150 --> 01:07:56.810
I told Jae Pil we should break up

01:07:56.810 --> 01:08:00.850
saying things I didn't even mean? Why?

01:08:07.010 --> 01:08:09.770
What are you saying?

01:08:11.900 --> 01:08:17.900
You broke up with Jae Pil because of me?

01:08:20.630 --> 01:08:23.370
I knew.

01:08:25.270 --> 01:08:28.150
I knew you liked him.

01:08:29.960 --> 01:08:34.920
I knew everything back then.

01:08:37.880 --> 01:08:39.630
Jong Hui.

01:08:40.670 --> 01:08:44.200
But I shouldn't have.

01:08:45.990 --> 01:08:49.190
I should've turned a blind eye
and stayed with him.

01:08:50.740 --> 01:08:52.530
You...

01:08:54.040 --> 01:08:57.230
You have a family who really loves you,

01:08:57.230 --> 01:09:01.270
Jeong Bun, and Ho Suk. But I...

01:09:03.520 --> 01:09:04.930
What...

01:09:05.930 --> 01:09:08.600
What did I have to be so proud of?

01:09:10.220 --> 01:09:13.030
I didn't have anything to show for.

01:09:15.650 --> 01:09:21.270
♫ To me, you are ♫

01:09:23.260 --> 01:09:26.580
I have nothing.

01:09:29.060 --> 01:09:37.050
♫ Meeting at the end of the brokenness ♫

01:09:37.050 --> 01:09:43.500
♫ Like any ordinary sunlight ♫

01:09:53.850 --> 01:09:57.880
Time flies, doesn't it?

01:09:57.880 --> 01:10:01.050
Feels like Yeong Rye entered
training just yesterday,

01:10:01.050 --> 01:10:02.610
and the pageant is here already.

01:10:02.610 --> 01:10:05.580
They said they're taping the preshow today.

01:10:05.580 --> 01:10:08.230
What's so fast about it?

01:10:08.230 --> 01:10:11.950
For Jae Pil, the last three weeks
must've felt like three years.

01:10:11.950 --> 01:10:15.550
Totally. Oppa has been moping
around with that long face.

01:10:15.550 --> 01:10:17.370
I guess it's Yeong Rye over me now.

01:10:17.370 --> 01:10:20.810
Of course. You like Yeong Bae over me now, too.

01:10:22.430 --> 01:10:26.260
Isn't this going to tangle
the family tree like crazy?

01:10:26.260 --> 01:10:28.160
What if we end up double in-laws someday?

01:10:28.160 --> 01:10:30.020
You're getting ahead of yourself again.

01:10:30.020 --> 01:10:32.760
They're middle schoolers,
and you're talking double in-laws.

01:10:32.760 --> 01:10:37.170
Hey, you never know with people. Right?

01:10:37.170 --> 01:10:40.620
I'm in favor. What's wrong with double in-laws?

01:10:42.440 --> 01:10:45.830
Anyway, Yeong Rye must be so nervous right now.

01:10:45.830 --> 01:10:49.790
Even my heart is pounding like crazy.

01:11:18.560 --> 01:11:21.000
[1989, 33rd Miss Korea Preshow Event]

01:11:21.000 --> 01:11:23.950
- What's that?
- Look this way.

01:11:23.950 --> 01:11:26.170
You need to do this well.

01:11:26.170 --> 01:11:28.750
- I'll fix it for you.
- No, it's good.

01:11:28.750 --> 01:11:30.650
It looks unbalanced here.

01:11:30.650 --> 01:11:32.280
Look ahead.

01:11:33.340 --> 01:11:36.180
Be sure to smile starting now.

01:11:37.410 --> 01:11:39.960
Confidence comes from posture,

01:11:39.960 --> 01:11:43.020
and ease comes from the smile.

01:11:43.020 --> 01:11:45.490
Shoulders back and brace your core.

01:11:45.490 --> 01:11:46.810
Good.

01:11:47.710 --> 01:11:51.550
Gosh! Why isn't the makeup setting today?

01:11:51.550 --> 01:11:53.260
This is driving me crazy.

01:11:53.260 --> 01:11:54.900
Your dark circles-

01:11:55.900 --> 01:11:58.500
are so heavy.

01:11:58.500 --> 01:12:01.810
You couldn't sleep last night, Jong Hui?

01:12:02.810 --> 01:12:04.970
No, not much.

01:12:04.970 --> 01:12:08.340
Concealer. Hurry up and conceal.

01:12:08.340 --> 01:12:09.820
Hurry!

01:12:11.510 --> 01:12:13.920
All right, everyone. Attention, please.

01:12:13.920 --> 01:12:15.840
The representative of our sponsor,

01:12:15.840 --> 01:12:19.290
who has been supporting this year's Miss Korea,

01:12:19.290 --> 01:12:20.930
is here to cheer you on.

01:12:20.930 --> 01:12:23.220
Let's greet him.

01:12:23.220 --> 01:12:25.420
Sir, this way.

01:12:30.940 --> 01:12:32.640
Hello.

01:12:32.640 --> 01:12:35.600
I am Jeong Hyeon, CEO of Hwashin Apparel.

01:12:35.600 --> 01:12:37.400
Oh, wow!

01:12:42.550 --> 01:12:45.610
How did this happen?

01:12:45.610 --> 01:12:48.730
How are you a sponsor's representative?

01:12:49.700 --> 01:12:52.800
It worked out that way. I didn't push for it.

01:12:52.800 --> 01:12:57.930
My father set it up, and it ended up
with me when I took over Apparel.

01:12:57.930 --> 01:13:00.820
I did decline being a judge, though.

01:13:00.820 --> 01:13:03.930
I wasn't sure I could set aside personal feelings.

01:13:03.930 --> 01:13:05.620
That's too bad.

01:13:05.620 --> 01:13:09.240
If you were a judge, I'd have it in the bag.

01:13:09.240 --> 01:13:12.120
Really? Should I say yes now?

01:13:12.120 --> 01:13:14.590
No, no.

01:13:16.830 --> 01:13:22.290
I was nervous, but seeing you
makes me feel much better.

01:13:22.290 --> 01:13:23.520
I'm energized.

01:13:23.520 --> 01:13:25.070
Good.

01:13:26.800 --> 01:13:31.160
Do you know where Daddy-Long-Legs gets his name?

01:13:31.160 --> 01:13:34.270
Not sure. I don't really remember.

01:13:34.270 --> 01:13:38.140
Because when he turns away,
only a long shadow remains.

01:13:42.080 --> 01:13:44.190
I'm not judging,

01:13:44.190 --> 01:13:47.240
but remember that I will always be behind you

01:13:47.240 --> 01:13:50.260
like that shadow and do well. Okay?

01:13:54.530 --> 01:14:00.770
To be honest, I've been meaning to see you, Oppa.

01:14:01.800 --> 01:14:05.400
- What you told me last time-
- Forget it.

01:14:10.250 --> 01:14:11.810
I know.

01:14:16.810 --> 01:14:20.690
All right. Let's focus on this pageant right now.

01:14:22.530 --> 01:14:25.490
I'll give you a hug for good luck.

01:14:33.280 --> 01:14:36.670
Break a leg, Ugly.

01:14:42.900 --> 01:14:46.300
[1989, 33rd Miss Korea Preshow Event]

